11/01/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH)-- BiH House of Representatives Speaker Nikola Spiric said Saturday (10 January) that state leaders will take more aggressive measures in fighting terrorist networks. Commenting on allegations concerning the participation of Bosnians in international terrorist organisations, Spiric admitted certain groups in the country might have been used for sheltering members of suspicious organisations or terror recruitment campaigns. (Nezavisne Novine, BH Radio, SRNA, BBC - 10/01/04)
